  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-09-18",
    "date": "2007-12-07T15:33:23Z",
    "text": "Fair Home Health Care Act of 2007 - Amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to exempt certain home health care workers who are employed on a casual basis from the minimum wage and maximum hour requirements under such Act. Defines employment on a \"casual basis\" as employment which is irregular or intermittent and does not exceed 20 hours per week in the aggregate."
  },
